def: "A zinc group element atom with a symbol Cn and atomic number 112. All its isotopes are intensely radioactive. Prior to its discovery, it had the placeholder name ununbium (in accordance with IUPAC recommendations). Following its discovery (in Darmstadt, 1996) and subsequent confirmation, the name copernicium was adopted in 2010." []
is_a: CHEBI:33521 ! metal atom

[Term]
id: CHEBI:33521
name: metal atom
def: "An atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity." []
is_a: CHEBI:33250 ! atom

[Term]
id: CHEBI:33839
name: macromolecule
def: "A macromolecule is a molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass." []
is_a: CHEBI:23367 ! molecular entity
relationship: BFO:0000051 BFO:0000040 ! has part material entity

[Term]
id: CHEBI:37376
name: tetraphosphorus decaoxide
is_a: CHEBI:23367 ! molecular entity

[Term]
id: CHEBI:49475
name: argon atom
is_a: CHEBI:23367 ! molecular entity
is_a: CHEBI:25585 ! nonmetal atom

[Term]
id: CHEBI:49631
name: gallium atom
def: "A metallic element predicted as eka-aluminium by Mendeleev in 1870 and discovered by Paul-Emile Lecoq de Boisbaudran in 1875. Named in honour of France (Latin <em>Gallia</em>) and perhaps also from the Latin <em>gallus</em> cock, a translation of Lecoq." []
is_a: CHEBI:33521 ! metal atom

[Term]
id: CHEBI:49637
name: hydrogen atom
is_a: CHEBI:23367 ! molecular entity
is_a: CHEBI:25585 ! nonmetal atom

