comment: A Portion Of Matter that consists of only tellurium atoms.
is_a: co:PMD_0020140 ! portion of pure chemical element
intersection_of: co:PMD_0020140 ! portion of pure chemical element
intersection_of: BFO:0000051 CHEBI:30452 {all_only="true"} ! has part tellurium atom
property_value: skos:definition "A 'portion of tellurium' is a 'portion of pure chemical element' that 'consists of' only chebi:tellurium atom." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010022
name: containing magnetic species
is_a: co:PMD_0000005 ! material property
property_value: skos:definition "A material property that inheres in a material entity in virtue of the presence of one or more magnetic species (e.g. ferromagnetic, paramagnetic, or diamagnetic particles or atoms), and that manifests under appropriate conditions as the ability of that material entity to exhibit a magnetic response or influence in a magnetic field." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010023
name: bioactive
is_a: BFO:0000016 ! disposition
property_value: skos:definition "A disposition that inheres in a material entity and is realized in an organismal context as a specific interaction with one or more biological systems, producing a measurable biological effect (e.g., therapeutic, toxic, or signaling outcome)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010024
name: bioinert
is_a: BFO:0000016 ! disposition
property_value: skos:definition "a disposition to elicit minimal or no biological response when in contact with tissue or implanted" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "non-toxic and non-immunogenic, with little or no bonding or integration with the body." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010025
name: bioresorbable
is_a: co:PMD_0020251 ! biocompatible
property_value: skos:comment "being absorbed or excreted as it performs its function, often eliminating the need for removal." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "biocompatibe and degrading and being resorbed by the body over time" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010026
name: organic composition
is_a: co:PMD_0025001 ! composition
property_value: skos:definition "A composition characterized by a primary molecular structure of carbon atoms covalently bonded to hydrogen (C-H bonds), typically forming linear, branched, or networked chains." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010027
name: inorganic composition
is_a: co:PMD_0025001 ! composition
property_value: skos:definition "material composition based on chemical elements other than those defining organic compounds, typically characterized by ionic or metallic bonding and the absence of a carbon-hydrogen ($C-H$) framework" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010029
name: specific strength
is_a: BFO:0000019 ! quality
property_value: skos:comment "SI unit for specific strength is Pa⋅m3/kg, or N⋅m/kg, which is dimensionally equivalent to m2/s2, In fiber or textile applications, tenacity is the usual measure of specific strength\n" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Specific strength is a quality that inheres in a material entity and is defined as the ratio of its tensile strength to its density." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010033
name: polymerization
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "The chemical process of reacting monomers, oligomers, or reactive precursors together to form longer macromolecular chains or three-dimensional networks" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010034
name: curing
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "The toughening or hardening of a polymer material by cross-linking of polymer chains." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010099
name: biomedical material
is_a: co:PMD_0000000 ! Material
relationship: RO:0000087 co:PMD_0010112 ! has role medical application role
property_value: skos:altLabel "biomaterial" xsd:string
property_value: skos:comment "related to the use of a material.   it is part of objects which participates some medical processes" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A non-living material intended to interface with biological systems to evaluate, treat, augment, or replace any tissue, organ, or function of the body." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010100
name: elemental semiconductor
is_a: co:PMD_0090000 ! semiconductor
relationship: RO:0002351 co:PMD_0020140 {cardinality="1"} ! has member portion of pure chemical element
property_value: skos:comment "Primarily includes group 14 elements like Silicon, Carbon, Germanium, Tin but also Selenium (group 16) and Boron (group 13)." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "semiconductor that shows semiconductive behavior as a pure element" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Silicon, Carbon, Germanium, alpha-Tin" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010101
name: compound semiconductor
is_a: co:PMD_0090000 ! semiconductor
intersection_of: co:PMD_0090000 ! semiconductor
intersection_of: RO:0002351 co:PMD_0020140 {minCardinality="2"} ! has member portion of pure chemical element
relationship: RO:0002351 co:PMD_0020140 ! has member portion of pure chemical element
property_value: skos:altLabel "alloy semiconductor" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "semiconductor which is composed of two or more pure elements" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "boron nitride (BN), gallium arsenide (GaAs), aluminium gallium arsenide (AlGaAs), indium gallium nitride (InGaN)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010102
name: organic semiconductor
is_a: co:PMD_0090000 ! semiconductor
relationship: RO:0000086 co:PMD_0010026 ! has quality organic composition
property_value: skos:definition "semiconductor which consists of   organic (carbon based) molecules or polymer" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010103
name: hybrid semiconductor
is_a: co:PMD_0090000 ! semiconductor
property_value: skos:definition "semiconductor which consists of organic semiconductors and non-organic semiconductors" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0010112
name: medical application role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "a role realized through the intentional interface with a biological system for the purpose of evaluating, treating, augmenting, or replacing any tissue, organ, or function of the body" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0011023
name: magnesia ceramic
is_a: co:PMD_0050055 ! oxide ceramic
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020067 ! has part portion of magnesium
property_value: skos:definition "oxide ceramic consisting primarily of magnesium oxide" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0011032
name: silicide ceramic
is_a: co:PMD_0050062 ! non-oxide ceramic
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020050 ! has part portion of silicon
property_value: skos:definition "non-oxide ceramic consisting of a silicon and another element" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0011034
name: cermet
is_a: co:PMD_0000120 ! metal matrix composite
property_value: skos:altLabel "ceramic-metal composite" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "metal matrix composite material consisting of a ceramic phase (typically carbides or nitrides) bonded with a continuous metallic phase" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020000
name: phase (thermodynamic)
is_a: BFO:0000040 ! material entity
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A thermodynamic phase is a material entity that forms a homogeneous portion of matter within a thermodynamic system and is characterized by uniform thermodynamic properties." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020001
name: filler role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Filler is the role of a 'PortionOfDisconnectedMatter' that implies being hosted in a matrix." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020002
name: precipitate role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Precipitate is the role of a portion of matter that implies being hosted in a matrix and the Precipitate derives from the matrix or the Precipitate derives from the thing that the matrix derives from." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020003
name: crystal
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
relationship: RO:0000086 co:PMD_0000591 ! has quality crystal structure
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A crystal is an object that has a quality \"crystal structure\"." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020004
name: composition data item
comment: These portions of other matters do not have to be portions of specific chemical elements, i.e., atomic composition, but rather portions of other substances, such as nitric acid and water.
relationship: RO:0002351 co:PMD_0025997 ! has member fraction value specification
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000116 "See editior note of composition to underatand the difference between composition and chemical composition data items.\n\nTo understand the difference between the composition and the composition data item, one has to understand the difference between SDCs and GDCs in BFO. A triple \"material entity has quality compsition\", conveys the fact such quality exists without telling us what are fractions of compounds in this material entity. A triple \"compostion is subject of composition data item\" conveys that there's an information about values of these fractions. Think of comosition data item as a pdf where the composition is documented." xsd:string
property_value: skos:altLabel "composition specification" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Composition data item is an information content entity that is about composition of a material enity. It has members fraction value specifications which specifiy values of propotions of compounds, which are parts of the material enity." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Nitric acid solution has quality  composition, and  the composition data item is about this composition.The composition data item has members fraction specifications of nitric acid, e.g., 4 vol.%, and distilled water. These fraction specifications specify value of pure substances of nitric acid and distilled water, respectively. Furthermore, these fraction specifications specify values of relational qualities (volume) proportion of nitric acid and (volume) proportion of distilled water." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020005
name: porosity
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "itensive quality embodiying the fraction of the materials (enclosing) spatial region occupied by pores." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020022
name: corrosion
comment: Corrosion is typically of interest when the change of the material affects the objects ability to fulfill its function.
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "corrosion is a slow chemical or electrochemical degradation process of a material entity due to its interaction with the surrounding environment." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020023
name: metallic grain structures
is_a: OBI:0001930 ! categorical value specification
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "The metallic grain structures is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the  metallic grain structure quality. It describes the morphology of polycrystalline metallic materials. Polycrystalline metallic materials will typically form their grain structures as one of those categories or a transition or mixture state of those." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020024
name: hydrogen bond
is_a: co:PMD_0050000 ! bond
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A hydrogen bond is a bond that binds one molecule’s hydrogen atom with the electronegative atoms of another molecule." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "The bond that forms between liquid water molecules at one molecules hydrogen ends and the other molecules oxygen end." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020025
name: obstacle role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "An obstacle role is a role of an independent continuant C that is realized in a motion process and indictes that C hinders the motion of a participant in the process." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "A precipitate or grain boundary may hinder the motion of a dislocation." xsd:string

