[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020098
name: nature constant
is_a: BFO:0000031 ! generically dependent continuant
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A nature constant is a generically dependent continuant whose value, maginitude or configuration is determined by nature including physics and mathematics." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Examples of nature constants are the speed of light, pi, etc." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020099
name: bravais lattice (3D)
comment: TODO: possibly extend for 2D (Graphene etc)\n\nMore elaborate crystal descriptions may be found in http://emmo.info/domain-crystallography/crystallography or https://purls.helmholtz-metadaten.de/disos/cso
is_a: OBI:0001930 ! categorical value specification
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "The bravais lattice is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the crystal structure quality. It describes the possible geometric arrangement of lattice points in a crystal. The present descriptor is limited to the 14 possible three-dimensional arrangements." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020101
name: proportion
is_a: BFO:0000145 ! relational quality
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0050000 ! bond
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "concentration" xsd:string
property_value: skos:altLabel "fraction" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A proportion is a relational quality between two entities (the whole and the part) which quantifies the relation between the whole and its part." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020102
name: mass proportion
is_a: co:PMD_0020101 ! proportion
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020103 ! molar proportion
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Mass proportion is a proportion which quantifies the mass of the part relative to the mass of the whole." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020103
name: molar proportion
is_a: co:PMD_0020101 ! proportion
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "Molar Ratio" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Molar proportion is the proportion which quantifies the entities count of the part in relation to the entities count of the whole." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "The molar ratio of hydrogen gas H2 molecules to water H2O molecules is 1/1 in the oxyhydrogen reaction. The molar ratio of oxygen molecules O2 to water molecules is 2/1.\nThe molar ratio of carbon dioxide to average atmosphere air is 420 ppm as of 2022 AD." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020104
name: volume proportion
is_a: co:PMD_0020101 ! proportion
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Volume proportion is a proportion which quantifies the volume of the part relative to the volume of the whole." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020105
name: geogenic mineral
is_a: co:PMD_0000127 ! mineral
intersection_of: co:PMD_0000127 ! mineral
intersection_of: RO:0002353 co:PMD_0000110 ! output of geological process
relationship: RO:0002353 co:PMD_0000110 ! output of geological process
property_value: skos:definition "material that is formed through geological processes" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "such as Quartz (Silicates) or calcite (Carbonate) or Feldspar (Aluminosilicate)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020106
name: polycrystal
is_a: co:PMD_0000890 ! connected material entity aggregate
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0000663 ! has part crystallite
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "Polycrystalline structure" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A polycrystal is a connected material entity aggregate that consists of multiple crystal grains joined through crystallographic interfaces." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020112
name: grain size distribution
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "An intensive quality describing the lower length scale object aggregate (grains) that is part of the material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020113
name: fluid (object)
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020170 ! Bramme
property_value: skos:definition "Fluid (object) is an object that consists of some portion of matter which bears an aggregate state that concretizes a liquid or gaseous aggregate state." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020114
name: medium role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "Medium role is a role beared by an object which implies that the object serves as an intermediary for the transmission of something else, like energy, force, or information." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Air in the air cooling process, N2 atmosphere in a furnace cooling process, oil in a quenching process, crystal lattice in a solid state diffusion" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020115
name: aerosol
is_a: co:PMD_0000891 ! disconnected material entity aggregate
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "An aerosol is a disconnected material entity aggregate which:\n1. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretizes gaseous and \n2. consists of some portion of matter whose aggregate state quality concretises solid or liquid (TODO: express that this portion is also a disconnected material entity aggregate)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020116
name: aggregate state value
is_a: OBI:0001930 ! categorical value specification
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "The aggregate state value is a categorical value specification that specifies value of the aggregate state quality." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020126
name: foam
is_a: co:PMD_0000890 ! connected material entity aggregate
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 "old defintion: A foam is a material entity aggregate that is also a composite material c. \nThe parts of c that have the filler role are vacuum-filled or gas filled pores. \nThe parts of c that have the matrix role consist of a material that is bearer of solid or liquid aggregate state. \nOne pore with its surrounding matrix is called 'cell'. \nDepending on the interconnectedness of the pores the foam is open- or closed-cell." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A foam is a connected material entity aggregate that consists of a solid or liquid matrix containing gas-filled or vacuum-filled pores forming cellular structures." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020128
name: thermodynamic system
is_a: BFO:0000027 ! object aggregate
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A thermodynamic system is an object aggregate whose objects are bearer of  thermodynamic properties. A thermodynamic system environs a thermodynamic process by which the thermodynamic properties of the objects of the thermodynamic system change over time." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020129
name: reversible process
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A reversible process is a process whose participants form a thermodynamic system with an entropy S and S remains constant during the process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020130
name: driving force of phase in system
is_a: BFO:0000145 ! relational quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Driving force of phase in a system is a relational quality that inheres between two material entities, the species and the material (system). The driving force is a factor that promotes a physical process or (eletro-)chemical reaction in a material (system) to occur and proceed towards completion. It can be quantified as the gradient of the activity of the participating species." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "For α → β: ΔG = G_β − G_α. If ΔG < 0, the transformation is thermodynamically favorable; many report the driving force as F = −ΔG > 0" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020131
name: intensive quality
is_a: BFO:0000019 ! quality
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020148 ! extensive quality
relationship: RO:0000080 co:PMD_0000001 {comment="Due to the duality of object and portion of matter this axiom can not be an equivalent class axiom."} ! quality of portion of matter
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "Point property" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "An intensive quality is a quality that inheres in only portion of matter and thus is independent of the bearers (system-) size." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020132
name: size
is_a: co:PMD_0020148 ! extensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "an extensive quality of a material entity that describes its spatial extend." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020133
name: mass
comment: Mass is relevant in such processes as gravitation, acceleration, etc.
is_a: co:PMD_0020148 ! extensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Mass is fundamental extensive quality." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020134
name: stimulus role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "The stimulus role is a role that an object bears in a process when causally influencing another object  that bears a stimulation target role in the same process. 'Role' implies here, that the 'bearing' assignment depends on the intent." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020135
name: stimulation target role
is_a: co:PMD_0000975 ! Proben-Rolle
property_value: skos:definition "See 'Stimulus role'" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020136
name: phase transformation
comment: The number of phases involved can vary as well as the mechanisms involved can be different.
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A thermodynamic phase transformation is a process in/of a thermodynamic system, that involves the transformation of phases of the system to other phases." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020137
name: stable phase
comment: See metastable phase
is_a: co:PMD_0020000 ! phase (thermodynamic)
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020149 ! metastable phase
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A stable phase is a phase that does not have a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" in the \"pmd:phase transformation\" it participates." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "A phase that participates in a phase transformation pt and pt that is not a metastable phase." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020138
name: lot
is_a: BFO:0000027 ! object aggregate
property_value: skos:definition "A lot is an object aggregate whose parts are output of the same production process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020139
name: Schmelze
is_a: co:PMD_0020113 ! fluid (object)
property_value: skos:definition "is a fluid (object) with a disposition to realize a blank role in a manufacturing process" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "molten PLA in a 3D printing process" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020140
name: portion of pure chemical element
is_a: CHEBI:60003 ! pure substance
property_value: skos:definition "A portion of pure chemical element is a pure substance composed of multiple atoms, which are all of the same kind." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020141
name: fatigue (reaction to repetitive loading)
comment: Fatigue is typically of interest when the change of the material affects the objects ability to fulfill its function.
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "fatigue is a process that affects an material entities integrity by nucleation and growing cracks." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020142
name: energy
is_a: co:PMD_0020148 ! extensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 OEO:00000150
property_value: skos:definition "an extensive quality of material entities which manifests as a capacity to perform work (such as causing motion or the interaction of molecules)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020143
name: process chain
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "A process chain is a process that 'has continuant part' subprocesses S1...Sn where S1...Sn precede each other and where some object or object aggregate that are output of Sn are then input to Sn+1." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020144
name: product (chemical reaction)
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "Product is the role of a material entity that is output of a chemical reaction and is created or transformed during the reaction." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020145
name: educt
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "Educt is the role of a material entity that is input of a chemical reaction and is consumed or transformed during the reaction" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020146
name: catalyst
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "Catalyst is the role of a participant in a chemical reaction that does not alter its qualities/realizable entities  after the chemical reaction." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020147
name: eutectoid phase transformation
comment: It is defined on the phase diagram at fixed composition and typically proceeds by diffusion‑controlled nucleation and growth (e.g., γ → α + Fe3C producing pearlite in steels).
is_a: co:PMD_0020136 ! phase transformation
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A eutectoid phase transformation is a phase transformation in which a solid parent phase of eutectoid composition decomposes into two distinct solid daughter phases at constant temperature and pressure." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020148
name: extensive quality
is_a: BFO:0000019 ! quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "An extensive quality is a quality that inheres in only object or object aggregate or fiat object part or chemical entity and is dependent on the bearers (system-) size." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020149
name: metastable phase
comment: The stability of a phase can only be evaluated in the context of a (possibly unknown) phase transformation process.
is_a: co:PMD_0020000 ! phase (thermodynamic)
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A metastable phase phase_trans is a phase that has a \"pmd:disposition of a phase to transform\" disp_trans and disp_trans is realized in a \"pmd:phase transformation\" proc_trans and proc_trans has participant sys_trans and sys_trans has part phase_trans." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020150
name: volume
is_a: co:PMD_0020132 ! size
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Volume is a three dimensional size." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020151
name: internal energy
is_a: co:PMD_0020142 ! energy
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020155 ! interatomic interaction energy
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Internal energy is a universal extensive quality that specifies the bearers potential to do work." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020152
name: component
is_a: BFO:0000027 ! object aggregate
property_value: skos:definition "A component is an object aggregate that bears a function in a technical system." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020153
name: technical system
is_a: BFO:0000027 ! object aggregate
relationship: BFO:0000051 BFO:0000030 ! has part object
relationship: OBI:0000312 co:PMD_0000833 ! is specified output of Herstellungsprozess
relationship: RO:0000085 BFO:0000034 ! has function function
property_value: skos:definition "A technical system is an object aggregate: \n1. that is output of a manufacturing process, \n2. that has some function \n3. whose continuant parts are some components." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020154
name: precipitation (phase)
comment: It proceeds by nucleation and growth.
is_a: co:PMD_0020136 ! phase transformation
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Precipitation from a supersaturated solid solution is a phase transformation process in which a single supersaturated parent phase decomposes into a solute‑depleted matrix and dispersed, compositionally distinct precipitate phases." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020155
name: interatomic interaction energy
is_a: co:PMD_0020142 ! energy
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Interatomic interaction energy is added/removed from the atom aggregate if one atom is moved infinitely away from the rest of the aggregate." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020156
name: peritectic phase transformation
comment: It is marked on phase diagrams by a peritectic point and proceeds by an interfacial, diffusion‑controlled reaction that is often kinetically sluggish, leading to incomplete transformation or complex microstructures during solidification.
is_a: co:PMD_0020136 ! phase transformation
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A peritectic phase transformation is a phase transformation in which a liquid parent phase and an existing solid phase react on cooling to form a different solid phase (L + α → β)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020157
name: spinodal decomposition
comment: Unlike nucleation and growth transformations, it has no nucleation barrier and proceeds by uphill diffusion and wavelength‑selective amplification of composition modulations, producing an interconnected, compositionally modulated microstructure that coarsens over time.
is_a: co:PMD_0020136 ! phase transformation
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Spinodal decomposition is a diffusion‑controlled  continuous phase transformation in which a single homogeneous solution spontaneously separates into two compositionally distinct phases by amplification of infinitesimal concentration fluctuations." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020158
name: parent phase role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020159 ! daughter phase role
property_value: skos:definition "The parent phase role is the role of a phase that dissolves during the phase transformation process. As such, the bearer is a metastable phase." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020159
name: daughter phase role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "The daughter phase role is the role of a phase that forms during the phase transformation process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020160
name: microconstituent (phase mixture)
comment: In metallography the term phase is sometimes used to denote microconstituents. To avoid confusion, the term phase should only be used for thermodynamic phases.
is_a: co:PMD_0000001 ! portion of matter
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A portion of matter that has one or more thermodynamic phases arranged in a characteristic spatial configuration (morphology) as parts." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Pearlite is a microconstituent that has as parts the thermodynamic phases ferrite (α-Fe) and cementite (Fe3C) as parts. The characteristic spatial arrangement is in that case the lamellar orientation of the phases.\n\nMartensite is a microconstituent that has as part the thermodynamic ferrite phase with characteristic morphologies and chemistry. Its presence and amount is governed by the processing path and kinetics." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020161
name: activity (thermodynamic)
is_a: BFO:0000145 ! relational quality
property_value: IAO:0000119 "old defintion: \nActivity (a_X) is a relational property between a chemical species X and a non-ideal solution. a_X is a measure of the effective concentration of a chemical species X in the non-ideal solution, accounting for interactions between particles. It is defined as the product of the concentration and an activity coefficient, where the activity coefficient corrects for non-ideal behavior." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Thermodynamic activity is a relational quality that inheres between a chemical species and a non-ideal solution and represents the effective concentration of the species accounting for particle interactions." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020162
name: activation energy
is_a: co:PMD_0000008 ! process attribute
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "Activation energy (E_a) a process attribute characterizing the minimum amount of energy required to initiate a reaction, allowing educts to overcome an energy barrier to transform into products." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020163
name: eutectic phase transformation
is_a: co:PMD_0020136 ! phase transformation
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A eutectic phase transformation is a phase transformation in which a liquid parent phase decomposes into two distinct solid daughter phases at constant temperature and pressure." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020164
name: state of matter boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0000882 ! phase boundary (realization)
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020167 ! structural boundary
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A state of matter boundary is a phase boundary that is realized by the transition from one aggregate state to another aggregate state." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020165
name: disposition of a phase to transform
comment: The disposition is grounded in the phases activity in the thermodynamic system in question.
is_a: BFO:0000016 ! disposition
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "The disposition of a phase to transform into another phase in a phase transformation process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020166
name: heat (metallurgy)
property_value: skos:definition "A heat is a fixed amount of metallic alloy that may be input to some manufacturing process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020167
name: structural boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0000882 ! phase boundary (realization)
property_value: skos:definition "Structural phase boundary is a phase boundary that is realized in the transition from one structure to another structure." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "ɑ-Ɣ transformation in iron at 910 °C" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020168
name: magnetic boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0000882 ! phase boundary (realization)
property_value: skos:definition "A magnetic boundary is a phase boundary that is realized by the transition from one magnetic ordering to another magnetic ordering." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020169
name: mixture boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0000882 ! phase boundary (realization)
property_value: skos:definition "A mixture boundary is a phase boundary that is realized by the transition from one phase to another phase in a system involving also chemical variations." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020170
name: Bramme
comment: The ingot may be hot rolled after casting...
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "An ingot is an object that has a thick section and may bear a semi finished product role and that is the specified output of a casting process. At the same time it is a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020171
name: phase boundary (spatial)
is_a: BFO:0000146 ! fiat surface
property_value: IAO:0000116 "Should it have exactly two phases as member parts?" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A fiat surface separating one phase from another phase." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "The phase boundary between liquid and the gaseous phase in a tank. \nThe phase boundary between Fe3C and Fe of a pearlite lamellae." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020172
name: sheet
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A plate is a thin rectangular object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it is a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020173
name: billet
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A billet is a relatively compact object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it is a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020174
name: foil
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A plate is a very thin rectangular object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020175
name: coil (coiled sheet)
comment: Coils may have several sheets that are joined together.
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A coil is an object that has part some sheets or foils. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020176
name: plate
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A plate is a thick rectangular object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020177
name: bar
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A bar is a long object with rectangular section that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020178
name: rod
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A rod is a long object with oval or round section that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020179
name: wire (semi finished product)
comment: This class does not include cables or other compound structures.
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A wire is a long and somewhat flexible object that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it is a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020180
name: tube
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A tube is a long object with a hollow section and moderate wall thickness that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020181
name: pipe
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A tube is a long object with a hollow section and pronounced wall thickness that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020182
name: profile (semi finished product)
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A profile is a long object with determined section shape that may bear a semi finished product role. At the same time it may be a material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020183
name: Recker
is_a: co:PMD_0000648 ! Formmaschine
property_value: skos:definition "A strech straightener machine is a forming machine that is used in a \"forming under tensile conditions\" process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020184
name: Walzwerk
is_a: co:PMD_0000602 ! Gerät
property_value: skos:definition "A rolling mill is a device that has part some rolling stand and whose specified input participates in some forming process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020185
name: rolling stand
is_a: co:PMD_0000602 ! Gerät
property_value: skos:definition "A rolling stand is a device that is part of a rolling mill, has some work rolls and participates in a rolling pass." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Ein Walzstock ist ein Teil eines Walzwerks, hat als Teil Arbeitswalzen und nimmt Teil an einen Walzstich." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020186
name: aluminium alloy
is_a: co:PMD_0010007 ! non-ferrous metal
is_a: co:PMD_0025004 ! alloy
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020071 ! has part portion of aluminium
property_value: skos:definition "non-ferrous metal consisting primarily of aluminium mixed with other elements" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020187
name: copper alloy
is_a: co:PMD_0010007 ! non-ferrous metal
is_a: co:PMD_0025004 ! alloy
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020054 ! has part portion of copper
property_value: skos:definition "non-ferrous metal consisting primarily of copper combined with other elements" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020188
name: nickel alloy
is_a: co:PMD_0010007 ! non-ferrous metal
is_a: co:PMD_0025004 ! alloy
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020051 ! has part portion of nickel
property_value: skos:definition "non-ferrous metal consisting primarily of nickel combined with other elements" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020189
name: titanium alloy
is_a: co:PMD_0010007 ! non-ferrous metal
is_a: co:PMD_0025004 ! alloy
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020095 ! has part portion of titanium
property_value: skos:definition "non-ferrous metal consisting primarily of titanium combined with other elements" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020190
name: metallographic section (surface)
is_a: co:PMD_0000965 ! surface layer (fiat object part)
property_value: skos:definition "A surface layer (fiat object part) of an object which at the same time is a metal and the object is specified output of a planned process which describes the preparation of the surface." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020191
name: metallographic section (embedded sample)
comment: Typical dimensions of the round mountings are a diameter of 20-50 mm and a thickness of 10-20 mm.
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A metallographic section (embedded sample) is an object that has two parts: a metallic object that has a metallographic section (surface) as part and the mounting which is produced during a hot embedding or cold embedding process." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020192
name: macrosection (metallography)
is_a: co:PMD_0020190 ! metallographic section (surface)
property_value: skos:definition "A macrosection (metallography) is a metallographic section (surface) that is produced directly on an object. The object may be cut in order to make accessible a section (fiat surface) of interest." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020193
name: tensile testpiece
is_a: BFO:0000030 ! object
property_value: skos:definition "A tensile testpiece is a longitudinal object that has two parts which were designed for gripping (gripping section) at its ends and a part between the gripping sections that has been designed to observe the materials or the objects reaction to tensile loading." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020194
name: diffusion
comment: often used to describe mass transport from regions of high concentration to regions of low concentration
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "process by which material entities spread or move due to random thermal motion" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020195
name: crystallization
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "process by which a solid with long-range order forms" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020196
name: recrystallization
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "process in which a new, defect-free grain structure forms in a material from an existing deformed grain structure." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020197
name: lattice point
is_a: BFO:0000147 ! fiat point
property_value: skos:definition "A lattice point is a fiat point that represents a position in a crystal lattice at which structural entities are regularly arranged." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020198
name: interstitial site
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
property_value: skos:definition "An interstitial site is a site that is located between regular lattice points in a crystal structure." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020199
name: slip plane
is_a: BFO:0000146 ! fiat surface
property_value: skos:definition "A slip plane is a fiat surface that corresponds to a crystallographic plane of a 3D crystal along which dislocations can glide" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020200
name: force
is_a: BFO:0000017 ! realizable entity
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Old definition: Force is a reciprocal relation realized between two objects where the other object exerts the same force with opposite sign onto the first. Force may be responsible for changes in velocity and/or deformation of objects." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "A force is a realizable entity that consists of a reciprocal interaction between two objects and is realized as equal and opposite influences capable of changing motion or causing deformation." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020201
name: section
is_a: BFO:0000146 ! fiat surface
property_value: skos:definition "Section is a planar fiat surface cutting across the object" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020202
name: crack
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020203 ! notch
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A crack is a site that consists of a physical separation within a material entity occurring at the level of atomic bonds." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020203
name: notch
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A notch is a site that consists of a geometric surface feature of an object characterized by a strong local change in shape or cross-section." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020204
name: pore
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A pore is a site that consists of a cavity located within the bulk of a material entity." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020205
name: defect role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A defect role is a role of an independent continuant C indicating that C may affect a material entity E's ability to realize a function. C is continuant part of E." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "A crack in an structural member may affect its ability to carry a load." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020206
name: unit cell (3D crystal)
is_a: BFO:0000028 ! three-dimensional spatial region
property_value: skos:definition "A unit cell (3D crystal) is a three-dimensional spatial region that represents the smallest repeating region whose spatial translation reproduces a crystal lattice." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020207
name: amount of substance
is_a: co:PMD_0020103 ! molar proportion
property_value: skos:definition "Amount of substance n is a molar proportion when the whole is an object aggregate N, which has avogadro number objects (of same type) as parts (n = N/N_A)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020208
name: slip direction
is_a: BFO:0000142 ! fiat line
property_value: skos:definition "A slip direction is a fiat line that corresponds to the crystallographic direction along which dislocations glide os a slip plane." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020209
name: slip system (3D)
comment: Is determined by the Bravais lattice.
is_a: OBI:0001930 ! categorical value specification
property_value: IAO:0000116 "TODO: Indiviuals for the possible values need to be created, similar to the values of the Bravais lattice value individuals." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "specifies the value of the crystal slip plane together with the slip direction." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020210
name: elemental crystal
is_a: co:PMD_0020003 ! crystal
relationship: RO:0002351 co:PMD_0020140 ! has member portion of pure chemical element
property_value: skos:definition "a crystal that consists of exactly one atomic species" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020211
name: allotropy of an elemental crystal
is_a: co:PMD_0020212 ! polymorphism of crystal
property_value: IAO:0000116 "different structures of a crystal could be linked by a relational property 'allotrope of'" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "a disposition of an elemental crystal to change its crystal structure" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020212
name: polymorphism of crystal
comment: stable structure depends on pressure and temperature
is_a: BFO:0000016 ! disposition
property_value: skos:definition "disposition of a crystal to change its crystal structure" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020213
name: grain boundary
is_a: BFO:0000146 ! fiat surface
property_value: skos:definition "A grain boundary is a fiat surface that separates adjacent grains in a polycrystalline material and is characterized by structural discontinuity." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "the part of a grain that is close to the grain boundary and possibly characterized by disorder is a fiat object part (grain surface layer)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020214
name: diffraction
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "is a process of interference of waves which, scattered by a material’s periodic features, produce characteristic patterns" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020215
name: wave
comment: may propagate through a medium or vacuum\ncharacterized by frequency, wavelength, and speed
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: skos:definition "is a process of a propagating of disturbance that transports energy and momentum" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020216
name: order scale value
is_a: OBI:0001930 ! categorical value specification
property_value: skos:definition "possible values of characteristic length over which structural correlations persist in a material" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020220
name: order scale
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
relationship: co:PMD_0000077 co:PMD_0020216 ! order scale value
property_value: skos:definition "characteristic length over which structural correlations persist in a material" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020221
name: self-diffusion in crystaline solid
is_a: co:PMD_0020194 ! diffusion
property_value: skos:definition "diffusion of entites of a single type in a crystal that consists of entites of this same type" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020222
name: inter-diffusion in crystalline solid
is_a: co:PMD_0020194 ! diffusion
property_value: skos:definition "diffusion of entites of some type in a crystal that consists mostly of entites of a different type" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020223
name: vacancy diffusion
is_a: co:PMD_0020194 ! diffusion
relationship: RO:0000057 co:PMD_0020224 ! has participant vacancy (crystal)
property_value: skos:definition "diffusion process in which crystal forming entities move from lattice points to vacant adjacent lattice points" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020224
name: vacancy (crystal)
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
relationship: owl:topObjectProperty co:PMD_0020197 ! lattice point
property_value: IAO:0000116 "TODO: replace topObjectProperty with occupies spatial region" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "site at lattice point at which the crystal forming entity is missing" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020225
name: interstitial diffusion
is_a: co:PMD_0020194 ! diffusion
property_value: skos:definition "diffusion process in which material entities move from interstitial sites to adjacent interstitial sites" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020226
name: flow
is_a: co:PMD_0000008 ! process attribute
relationship: co:PMD_0025006 co:PMD_0020246 ! continous transport
property_value: skos:definition "amount of transported entites per time" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020227
name: solute role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
disjoint_from: co:PMD_0020228 ! solvent role
property_value: skos:definition "role of an entity that is present in minor concentration in a solution" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020228
name: solvent role
is_a: BFO:0000023 ! role
property_value: skos:definition "role of an entity that is present in major concentration in a solution" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020229
name: solution
is_a: co:PMD_0000001 ! portion of matter
property_value: skos:definition "A portion of matter that is homogeneous, made up of at least two entity types, one playing the role of sovlent and the others playing the role of solute" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020230
name: solid solution
is_a: co:PMD_0020229 ! solution
property_value: skos:definition "a solution with solid aggregate state" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020231
name: interstitital solid solution
is_a: co:PMD_0020230 ! solid solution
property_value: skos:definition "a solid solution whose solute entities are located in the interstitial sites" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020232
name: substitutional solid solution
is_a: co:PMD_0020230 ! solid solution
property_value: IAO:0000116 "TODO: replace topObjectProperty with bfo:occupies spatial region" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "a solid solution whose solute entities occupy lattice points" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020233
name: dislocation
is_a: BFO:0000029 ! site
property_value: skos:definition "a linear site in a cystal that interrupts the cystal ordering" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020234
name: screw dislocation
is_a: co:PMD_0020233 ! dislocation
property_value: skos:definition "a dislocation characterized by shearing the chrystal by one plane" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020235
name: edge dislocation
is_a: co:PMD_0020233 ! dislocation
property_value: skos:definition "a dislocation characterized by adding one extra half plane into the crystal lattice" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020236
name: mixed dislocation
is_a: co:PMD_0020234 ! screw dislocation
is_a: co:PMD_0020235 ! edge dislocation
intersection_of: co:PMD_0020234 ! screw dislocation
intersection_of: co:PMD_0020235 ! edge dislocation
property_value: skos:definition "a dislocation that spans edge dislocation as well as screw dislocation" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020237
name: Burgers vector
is_a: co:PMD_0020148 ! extensive quality
property_value: skos:definition "quality of a dislocation in terms of amount and direction in a specific crystal type" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020238
name: high angle grain boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0020213 ! grain boundary
property_value: skos:definition "a grain boundary whose adjacent crystalls have a high angle of misalignment" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020239
name: small angle grain boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0020213 ! grain boundary
property_value: skos:definition "a grain boundary whose adjacent crystalls have a small angle of misalignment" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020240
name: twin boundary
is_a: co:PMD_0020213 ! grain boundary
property_value: skos:definition "grain boundary without distorted lattice" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020241
name: angle of misalignment (crystallography)
is_a: co:PMD_0001035 ! angle
property_value: skos:definition "smallest rotation angle needed to rotate one crystal orientation to coincide with the neighboring orientation" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020243
name: grain size
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
relationship: RO:0000080 co:PMD_0020106 ! quality of polycrystal
property_value: IAO:0000116 "size values of indiviudal grains are properties of the respective objects" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "an intensive quality epitomizing the average size of the grains of a polycrystal" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020244
name: flux
is_a: co:PMD_0020226 ! flow
property_value: skos:definition "a flow of a unit-entity per unit time" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020245
name: transport
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: IAO:0000116 "the moved entity is passive, locomotion would be the active counterpart" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "is a process in which an entity being moved within or accross another entity" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020246
name: continous transport
is_a: co:PMD_0020245 ! transport
property_value: skos:definition "recurring transport of multiple entities, such that the transported entities are not being discretized anymore" xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "the flow of a liquid in a pipe, diffusion of a gas in different gas" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020247
name: dispersion
comment: dispersion in optical glass is a refraction dependent on wavelength
is_a: co:PMD_0000877 ! optical property
property_value: skos:definition "Optical property describing the wavelength dependent phase velocity." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020248
name: diffusion flux
is_a: co:PMD_0020244 ! flux
property_value: skos:definition "flux transported by diffusion" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020249
name: ceramic crystal
is_a: co:PMD_0020003 ! crystal
property_value: skos:definition "a crystal whose atomic entities have a ionic or a covalent bond" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020250
name: alloy crystal
is_a: co:PMD_0020003 ! crystal
property_value: skos:definition "a crystal whose atomic entities have a metallic bond" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0020251
name: biocompatible
is_a: co:PMD_0010023 ! bioactive
property_value: skos:definition "bioactive without causing harmful or unacceptable biological responses (toxicity, inflammation, immune reaction) and performce of its intended function or integration with the tissue." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025001
name: composition
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: co:PMD_0000064 "Composition is a collective property of a portion of matter, i.e., the triple portion of matter has quality composition holds. As \"has quality\" is an inverse  functional property, only one instance of portion of matter can have this specific composition. However, proportions describe the relation between the prortion of matter (the whole) and some compound (the part). Thus, the following triples hold: portion of matter has relational quality proportion; portion of matter has part some substance (or whatever is your part); substance has relational quality proportion. \"Has relational quality\" is not inverse functional, i.e., it can point to a single object from 2 distinct subjects." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000116 "There's a dfference between composition and chemical compositon for the following reason: chemical compositon is relevant when the mass/volume/mole proportions of chemical elements(!) are identified, whlist composition includes proportions of molecules, other pure chemical substances, or even proptions of objects (in an object aggregate)." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Composition is an intensive quality which defines types and proportions of compounds present in a material entity and is subject of some composition data item." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "4 vol.% nitric acid solution, Styrene-Butadiene-Styrene (SBS) Block Copolymer with 50 vol.% of both styrene and butadiene" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025002
name: chemical composition data item
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "chemical composition specification" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Chemical composition data item is an information content entity that is about composition of a portion of matter. It has members fraction value specifications which specifiy values of propotions of portions of (pure) chemical elements, which are parts of the portion of matter." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Steel has quality chemical composition , and the chemical composition data item is about the chemical composition .The chemical composition data item has members fraction specifications of iron and carbon. These fraction specifications specify value of portion of iron and portion of carbon respectively. Furthermore, these fraction specifications specify  values of relational qualities (mass) proportion of iron and (mass) proportion of carbon." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025003
name: metallic grain structure
comment: ferrite, austenite, martensite, etc.
is_a: co:PMD_0020131 ! intensive quality
relationship: co:PMD_0000077 co:PMD_0020023 ! metallic grain structures
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "false" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "intensive quality epitomizing the distinct phases in the microscopic structure of a metallic material." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025004
name: alloy
is_a: co:PMD_0000852 ! metal
intersection_of: co:PMD_0000852 ! metal
intersection_of: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020250 ! has part alloy crystal
relationship: BFO:0000051 co:PMD_0020250 ! has part alloy crystal
property_value: skos:definition "metal that has part a mixture of chemical elements of which at least one is a metallic element" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025005
name: 3D
is_a: IAO:0000027 ! data entity
property_value: skos:definition "A three-dimensional data item is a representation or analysis, commonly applied in studying material properties in its volume or describing a dependency of one variable on two other variables." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Orientation distribution function (ODF), potential energy landscape" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025007
name: frequency
is_a: co:PMD_0000008 ! process attribute
property_value: skos:definition "Frequency is a process attribute which characterizes the rate per second of oscillation or vibration." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Frequency of electromagnetic wave, Frequency of sound wave." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025008
name: Transmissionselektronenmikroskop
is_a: co:PMD_0000624 ! Elektronenmikroskop
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "TEM" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "An electron microscope that produces high-resolution images of a sample's internal structure by transmitting electrons through the sample." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Ein Elektronenmikroskop, das hochauflösende Bilder der inneren Struktur einer Probe erzeugt, indem es Elektronen durch die Probe strahlt." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025009
name: material reacting process
comment: material reacting process has always energy minimization as a driving force.
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
relationship: BFO:0000066 co:PMD_0000001 ! occurs in portion of matter
property_value: skos:definition "Material reacting process is a process which occurs in a portion of matter due to some of its disposition or behavioral material property which has realization in some  stimulating process. Both the material reacting process and stimulating process must be occurent parts of a planned process, if the planned process takes place." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025010
name: heating
is_a: co:PMD_0000549 ! change of temperature
property_value: skos:definition "Heating is a change of temperature which corresponds to the increase of temperature in the system or object." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025011
name: cooling
is_a: co:PMD_0000549 ! change of temperature
property_value: skos:definition "Cooling is a change of temperature which corresponds to the decrease of temperature in the system or object." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025012
name: analytical calculation
is_a: co:PMD_0000583 ! Datenverarbeitung
property_value: skos:definition "Analytical calculation is a computing process which has value specification or measurement datum as a specified output. It applies a closed-form mathematical expression or formula to a set it specified inputs (value specifications) without requiring stochastic sampling, iterative numerical solving, or data-driven training." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025014
name: single crystal
is_a: co:PMD_0020003 ! crystal
property_value: skos:definition "Single crystal is a crystal which is not part of a polycrystal and its boundaries are its external surfaces." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025015
name: portion of lanthanum
comment: 'portion of pure chemical element' and 'has part' only CHEBI:33336
is_a: co:PMD_0020140 ! portion of pure chemical element
intersection_of: co:PMD_0020140 ! portion of pure chemical element
intersection_of: BFO:0000051 CHEBI:33336 {all_only="true"} ! has part lanthanum atom
property_value: skos:definition "A portion of lanthanum is a portion of pure substance that has parts only chebi:lanthanum atom." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025016
name: Innendurchmesser
is_a: co:PMD_0050051 ! Durchmesser
property_value: skos:definition "Der Innendurchmesser ist die Länge einer geraden Linie von einer Innenfläche eines Objekts oder Raums zur anderen Seite seiner Innenfläche durch den Mittelpunkt eines Objekts oder Raums, wenn es eine Innen- und Außenfläche hat." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Inner diameter is a length of a straight line from one inner surface of an object or space to the other side of its inner surface through the center of an object or space when it has the inside and outside surface." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025017
name: Außendurchmesser
is_a: co:PMD_0050051 ! Durchmesser
property_value: skos:definition "Der Außendurchmesser ist die Länge einer geraden Linie von einer Außenfläche eines Objekts oder Raums zur anderen Seite seiner Außenfläche durch den Mittelpunkt eines Objekts oder Raums, wenn es eine Innen- und Außenfläche hat." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Outer diameter is a length of a straight line from one outer surface of an object or space to the other side of its outer surface through the center of an object or space when it has the inside and outside surface." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025018
name: geometric relational quality
is_a: BFO:0000145 ! relational quality
property_value: skos:definition "Geometric relational quality is a relational quality describing the geometric relation between two or more independent continuants." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "Elongation of a specimen after a tensile step, i.e., the specimen before and after the test. Angle between a rolling direction of a rolled material and the longitudinal side of a specimen." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025020
name: single fatigue testing process
is_a: co:PMD_0000849 ! Mechanische Eigenschaften Analyseverfahren
property_value: skos:definition "Mechanical property analyzing process that is an occurent part of a fatigue testing process (S-N testing process). A single fatigue testing process assesses how many cycles a material can withstand under the given loading." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025021
name: Stanzmachine
is_a: co:PMD_0000602 ! Gerät
property_value: IAO:0000119 "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stamping_press" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Eine Stanzmachine ist ein Werkzeug/Gerät zur Metallbearbeitung, das dazu dient, geschnittenes Metall durch Verformung mit einer Matrize zu formen." xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Stamping press is a metalworking device which is used to shape a cut metal by deforming it with a die." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0025997
name: fraction value specification
is_a: OBI:0001931 ! scalar value specification
relationship: RO:0002350 co:PMD_0020004 {all_only="true"} ! member of composition data item
property_value: skos:definition "Fraction value specification is a value specification that contains information about quantitative share of a part relative to a specified whole." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "2.05 wt.% of carbon in steel, 4 vol.% of nitric acid in a solution" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0040001
name: length
comment: Length is a size that describes the spatial extent of its bearer in one dimension.
is_a: co:PMD_0020132 ! size
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:altLabel "dimension" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "Length is a one dimensional size." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050000
name: bond
is_a: BFO:0000145 ! relational quality
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: skos:definition "A bond is a relational quality describing the force interaction between atoms." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050001
name: covalent bond
is_a: co:PMD_0050000 ! bond
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 https://sciencenotes.org/types-of-chemical-bonds/
property_value: skos:definition "A covalent bond is a bond that forms when nonmetal atoms share electrons to achieve a stable electron configuration." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "In a water molecule (H₂O), the hydrogen and oxygen atoms share electrons." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050002
name: metallic bond
is_a: co:PMD_0050000 ! bond
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 https://www.thoughtco.com/metallic-bond-definition-properties-and-examples-4117948
property_value: skos:definition "A metallic bond is a bond that forms between metal atoms, where electrons are shared in a \"sea\" of electrons that move freely around the metal ions. This type of bonding gives metals their characteristic properties such as conductivity and malleability." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050003
name: ionic bond
is_a: co:PMD_0050000 ! bond
property_value: co:PMD_0000060 "true" xsd:boolean
property_value: IAO:0000119 https://sciencenotes.org/types-of-chemical-bonds/
property_value: skos:definition "An ionic bond is a bond that occurs when one atom donates an electron to another atom, resulting in oppositely charged ions that attract each other." xsd:string
property_value: skos:example "An example is the interaction between the atoms of sodium chloride (NaCl), where the sodium atom donates an electron to a chlorine atom." xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050004
name: thermoplastic polymer
is_a: co:PMD_0000888 ! polymer
property_value: skos:definition "polymer that becomes moldable when heated and solidifies upon cooling" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050005
name: polyethylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050004 ! thermoplastic polymer
property_value: skos:definition "poylethylen is a thermoplastic polymer produced by polymerization of the monomer ethylene including further crosslinking and modifications using other comonomers; it excludes ultra hight molecular polyethylen" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050006
name: low-density polyethylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050005 ! polyethylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "PE-LD" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polyethylene that is characterized by a branched molecular structure and low density" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050007
name: high-density polyethylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050005 ! polyethylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "PE-HD" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polyethylene that is characterized by a linear molecular structure and high density" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050008
name: linear low-density polyethylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050005 ! polyethylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "PE_LLD" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polyethylene that is distinguished by its linear backbone with short-chain branching" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050009
name: polypropylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050004 ! thermoplastic polymer
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "PP" xsd:string
property_value: skos:altLabel "polyethene" xsd:string
property_value: skos:comment "this excludes ultra hight molecular polyethylen because very high molecular weight polyethylene is not thermoplastic anymore" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "thermoplastic polymer produced by polymerization of the monomer propylene including further crosslinking and modifications using other comonomers" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050010
name: isotactic polypropylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050009 ! polypropylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "iPP" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polypropylene in which all the methyl groups are aligned on the same side of the polymer chain" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050011
name: syndiotactic polypropylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050009 ! polypropylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "sPP" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polypropylene in which the methyl groups alternate regularly along the polymer chain" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050012
name: atactic polypropylene
is_a: co:PMD_0050009 ! polypropylene
property_value: co:PMD_0050117 "aPP" xsd:string
property_value: skos:definition "polypropylene in which the methyl groups are randomly distributed along the polymer chain" xsd:string

[Term]
id: co:PMD_0050013
